    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Water-based, matte paint made with pigment in a casein binder, which is a phosphoprotein of milk. Dry casein is hydrolyzed with alkalis (lime, borax, ammonia, or others) to form a clear viscous solution. Casein paints dry to a matte, brittle film that is insoluble in water and impervious to most paint strippers.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047822/MFA Conservation and Art Material Encyclopedia Online: CAMEO (2005-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000042701/Wehlte, Materials and Techniques of Painting (1982)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一種啞光的水性顏料，以顏料加在酪蛋白黏接劑（即牛奶的磷蛋白）中製成。乾燥的酪蛋白膠用鹼（石灰、硼砂、氨水或其它鹼性物質）水解，形成質清的黏稠溶液。酪蛋白膠乾燥後為啞光脆薄膜，既不溶於水，也不會被脫漆劑滲透。 </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Matte verf op waterbasis, gemaakt met pigment in een caseïnebinder: een fosfoproteïne van melk. Wanneer droge caseïne wordt gehydrolyseerd met alkali's (kalk, borax, ammonia of andere), ontstaat er een heldere viskeuze oplossing. Caseïneverf droogt op als een matte, brosse laag die niet oplosbaar is in water en bestand is tegen de meeste afbijtmiddelen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
